TITLE: Adding a Simple Greeting Prompt in Go
DESCRIPTION: This prompt template provides a friendly greeting message using the MCP framework. It declares a single optional argument 'name' and returns a prompt with an assistant role message greeting the specified name or defaults to 'friend'. Dependencies include MCP prompt constructs and Go context. The prompt facilitates reusable conversational patterns for greeting users.
SOURCE: https://github.com/mark3labs/mcp-go/blob/main/README.md#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
// Simple greeting prompt
s.AddPrompt(mcp.NewPrompt("greeting",
    mcp.WithPromptDescription("A friendly greeting prompt"),
    mcp.WithArgument("name",
        mcp.ArgumentDescription("Name of the person to greet"),
    ),
), func(ctx context.Context, request mcp.GetPromptRequest) (*mcp.GetPromptResult, error) {
    name := request.Params.Arguments["name"]
    if name == "" {
        name = "friend"
    }

    return mcp.NewGetPromptResult(
        "A friendly greeting",
        []mcp.PromptMessage{
            mcp.NewPromptMessage(
                mcp.RoleAssistant,
                mcp.NewTextContent(fmt.Sprintf("Hello, %s! How can I help you today?", name)),
            ),
        },
    ), nil
})
```

